author: Courier sports staff (noreply@couriernews.com)
title: Johnson, Thessing place 3rd at state
text: slideshow Russellville Cyclones tennis players Bryce Johnson and Carter Thessing placed third in the Class 6A State Tennis Tournament hosted at Russellville High School and Arkansas Tech University on Monday and Tuesday.Johnson and Thessing defeated Texarkana in the first round of the tournament before topping Benton in the quarterfinals to reach the semifinals.Johnson/Thessing lost 6-2, 6-2 to McKee/Edwards from Jonesboro in the semifinals but defeated Dooley/Slater from Siloam Springs 6-2, 6-4 for third place in the Class 6A doubles tournament.Sophomore Sophie Davis won her first round singles match but lost in the quarterfinals on Monday.
